    "crystal_structure": "Semi-crystalline; natural cellulose forms Iα/Iβ allomorphs, regenerated cellulose forms cellulose II, and cellulose III/IV are accessible via chemical treatment.",
    "chain_flexibility_notes": "Extensive interchain hydrogen bonding between parallel chains forms rigid microfibrils, giving cellulose its high stiffness and insolubility in water and most organic solvents.",
